\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {H.2}{\ignorespaces Learned decision boundaries in the $(\mu _{\text  {RUL}}, \sigma )$ plane. Left: uncertainty-aware (UA) agent. Right: blind agent with $\sigma $ zeroed out. Dark regions denote MAINTAIN, light regions denote WAIT. The UA boundary bends leftward (toward higher RUL) as $\sigma $ increases, showing a $\sigma $-conditional policy. The blind boundary is an almost vertical line because the agent has no access to $\sigma $.}}{104}{figure.H.2}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:app_decision_boundary}{{H.2}{104}{Learned decision boundaries in the $(\mu _{\text {RUL}}, \sigma )$ plane. Left: uncertainty-aware (UA) agent. Right: blind agent with $\sigma $ zeroed out. Dark regions denote MAINTAIN, light regions denote WAIT. The UA boundary bends leftward (toward higher RUL) as $\sigma $ increases, showing a $\sigma $-conditional policy. The blind boundary is an almost vertical line because the agent has no access to $\sigma $}{figure.H.2}{}}
